title: [stellar-sdk] Misc improvements 2
body:
## Changing an existing definition ([Docs](https://stellar.github.io/js-stellar-sdk/), Source: [SDK](https://github.com/stellar/js-stellar-sdk) & [BASE](https://github.com/stellar/js-stellar-sdk))

Changes:

- refactor: namespace FederationServer
- refactor: namespace Server
- refactor: namespace StellarBase
- feat: conditionally typed BalanceLine
- feat: Memo namespace & conditionally typed value
- fix: *CallBuilder are effectively abstract class
- fix: NetworkError
- fix: FastSigning, hash, sign, verify
- test: Memo


Breaking Changes:

- `FederationRecord` -> `FederationServer.Record`
- `FederationOptions` -> `FederationServer.Options`
- `*` -> `Server.*` for plenty of Server stuff.
- Requires Typescript 2.8


### Work to be done

This is a continued work since #31592. Here are the outstanding problems what I have noticed so far:

- feat: copy over comments from source for intellisense
- fix: split Operation.* interfaces into param* and option*
    SDK allows different values to be passed (e.g. `string | number`) to operation constructor. But properties in parsed operations always have only one of both types although uses the same interface, which is wrong.
- feat: introduce AccountId, PublicKey and Secret as types
    That's because at some places is confusing whenever you need an address of existing account, random publicKey or just a string. Comments and intellisense may help a lot:
    ```
    /**
    * 56-character long string, starts with G and passes StrKey.isValidEd25519PublicKey().
    * Do not confuse with AccountId.
    */
    export type PublicKey = string;

    /**
    * Like PublicKey, but also points to existing account on the given Network.
    */
    export type AccountId = string;
    ```
- feat: separate *Record from plain responses
    For example, server.submitTransaction() returns plain response instead of enhanced `*Record`s returned by `*CallBuilder`s and thus currently is typed wrong. Furthermore, all `*Record`s are just extending plain responses, and thus obviously separating them would make that clear. Also, it would allow to use plain responses, e.g. for a quick `fetch` call.

React does not allow components to render `undefined`, only `null` is permitted.  Returning `undefined` from the render method results in the error:

See also the discussion at https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/3738.
